      "verdict": "fabricated",
      "evidence": "logalyzer/web.py does not exist. There is no web interface in this codebase at all — it is a CLI-only tool. The file referenced in the issue is entirely fabricated."
    },
    "008": {
      "verdict": "fabricated",
      "evidence": "logalyzer/parser.py:parse_line() (lines 72-93) does not truncate input. It calls `line.strip()` and then `LOG_LINE_RE.match(line)` on the full line. There is no 8192-character limit or any truncation logic anywhere in the parser."
    },
