    },
    "010": {
      "verdict": "fabricated",
      "evidence": "logalyzer/io.py:load_iter() (lines 36-42) opens a file and iterates line-by-line. While concurrent calls on the same path would each open their own file handle (no shared state), the claim of a 'race between file-handle creation and iteration' is not a real issue — each call gets its own independent file handle. There is no shared mutable state that would cause corruption."
    },
