      "evidence": "logalyzer/aggregate.py:11-16 — `by_status()` simply iterates entries and increments `c[e.status] += 1`. There is no special handling of 3xx codes, no deduplication logic, and no double-counting. Each entry is counted exactly once regardless of status code. The claim about 'chained iterators' is irrelevant — Counter.update or += works correctly on any iterable."
